snippet: At least 16 people were killed across Iraq on Monday in car bombings, assassinations, roadside bomb blasts and attacks on security forces.
abstract: At least 16 people are killed across Iraq in car bombings, assassinations, roadside bomb blasts and attacks on security forces; attacks stoke fears that disparate insurgent groups around Iraq are trying to sow sectarian violence.
lead_paragraph: At least 16 people were killed across Iraq on Monday in car bombings, assassinations, roadside bomb blasts and attacks on security forces.
